      "text": "\nModern [[French Horn]]s are a perfect example of [[The Most Complex Which Can Be Made To Work]], usually consisting of two or three independent instruments sharing an entrance and exit, and selected with two or three thumb-operated levers, as well as having three or four levers operated by the first through third or fourth fingers, usually on the left hand. It is played facing backwards (the instrument, not the person) and with the right hand in the bell, usually. Yet, somehow, it produces one of the broadest spectrums of colors of all the instruments, save synthesizer and full drum section. In the hands of a wizard, it is the Voice of God. In the hands of most mere mortals, it's just plain dumb sounding. ",
